ion. If you fail to avoid the effect, you take force damage equal to 16 × the number of charges in the staff. Every other creature in the area must make a DC 17 Dexterity saving throw. On a failed save, a creature takes damage based on how far away it is: 10 ft. away or closer takes 8 × the number of charges in the staff; 11 to 20 ft. away takes 6 × the number of charges in the staff; 21 to 30 ft. away takes 4 × the number of charges in the staff. On a successful save, a creature takes half as much damage."
