  {
    "index": "spirit-seeker-totem-warrior",
    "name": "Spirit Seeker",
    "level": 3,
    "class": {
      "index": "barbarian",
      "name": "Barbarian",
      "url": ""
    },
    "subclass": {
      "index": "totem-warrior",
      "name": "Totem Warrior",
      "url": ""
    },
    "desc": [
      "At 3rd level when you adopt this path, you gain the ability to cast the beast sense and speak with animals spells, each as a ritual. You don't need material components for these spells, and you can't cast them except as rituals."
    ],
    "url": ""
  },
  {
    "index": "totem-spirit-totem-warrior",
    "name": "Totem Spirit",
    "level": 3,
    "class": {
      "index": "barbarian",
      "name": "Barbarian",
      "url": ""
    },
    "subclass": {
      "index": "totem-warrior",
      "name": "Totem Warrior",
      "url": ""
    },
    "desc": [
      "At 3rd level, you choose a totem spirit and gain its feature. You must make or acquire a physical totem object incorporating fur or feathers, claws, teeth, or bones of the totem animal. Choose: Bear (resistance to all damage except psychic while raging); Eagle (when raging and not wearing heavy armor: enemies provoke opportunity attacks if they Disengage; you can Dash as a bonus action); Wolf (allies have advantage on melee attacks against creatures within 5 feet of you while you rage)."
    ],
    "url": ""
  },
  {
    "index": "aspect-of-the-beast-totem-warrior",
    "name": "Aspect of the Beast",
    "level": 6,
    "class": {
      "index": "barbarian",
      "name": "Barbarian",
      "url": ""
    },
    "subclass": {
      "index": "totem-warrior",
      "name": "Totem Warrior",
      "url": ""
    },
    "desc": [
      "At 6th level, you gain a magical benefit based on the totem animal of your choice (need not match Totem Spirit). Bear: carrying capacity doubled and advantage on Strength checks to push, pull, lift, or break objects. Eagle: see up to 1 mile away with no difficulty in dim light or thick foliage; no perception disadvantage from extreme weather. Wolf: track at fast pace and stealthily move at normal pace (alone or with companions traveling stealthily)."
    ],
    "url": ""
  },
  {
    "index": "spirit-walker-totem-warrior",
    "name": "Spirit Walker",
    "level": 10,
    "class": {
      "index": "barbarian",
      "name": "Barbarian",
      "url": ""
    },
    "subclass": {
      "index": "totem-warrior",
      "name": "Totem Warrior",
      "url": ""
    },
    "desc": [
      "At 10th level, you can cast the commune with nature spell, but only as a ritual. When you do so, a spiritual version of one of the animals you chose for Totem Spirit or Aspect of the Beast appears to you to convey the information you seek."
    ],
    "url": ""
  },
  {
    "index": "totemic-attunement-totem-warrior",
    "name": "Totemic Attunement",
    "level": 14,
    "class": {
      "index": "barbarian",
      "name": "Barbarian",
      "url": ""
    },
    "subclass": {
      "index": "totem-warrior",
      "name": "Totem Warrior",
      "url": ""
    },
    "desc": [
      "At 14th level, you gain a major totem feature based on the totem animal of your choice. Bear: while raging, hostile creatures within 5 feet have disadvantage on attack rolls against targets other than you or another character with this feature (creature must be able to see or hear you and not be incapacitated). Eagle: while raging, you have a flying speed equal to your current walking speed; can only use at the end of your turn (or you fall). Wolf: while raging, you can use a bonus action on your turn to knock a Large or smaller creature prone when you hit it with a melee weapon attack."
    ],
    "url": ""
  },
  {
    "index": "bonus-proficiencies-college-of-valor",
    "name": "Bonus Proficiencies",
    "level": 3,
    "class": {
      "index": "bard",
      "name": "Bard",
      "url": ""
    },
    "subclass": {
      "index": "college-of-valor",
      "name": "College of Valor",
      "url": ""
    },
    "desc": [
      "When you join the College of Valor at 3rd level, you gain proficiency with medium armor, shields, and martial weapons."
    ],
    "url": ""
  },
  {
    "index": "combat-inspiration-college-of-valor",
    "name": "Combat Inspiration",
    "level": 3,
    "class": {
      "index": "bard",
      "name": "Bard",
      "url": ""
    },
    "subclass": {
      "index": "college-of-valor",
      "name": "College of Valor",
      "url": ""
    },
    "desc": [
      "Also at 3rd level, you learn to inspire others in battle. A creature that has a Bardic Inspiration die from you can roll that die and add the number rolled to a weapon damage roll it just made. Alternatively, when an attack roll is made against the creature, it can use its reaction to roll the Bardic Inspiration die and add the number rolled to its AC against that attack, after seeing the roll but before knowing whether it hits or misses."
    ],
    "url": ""
  },
  {
    "index": "extra-attack-college-of-valor",
    "name": "Extra Attack",
    "level": 6,
    "class": {
      "index": "bard",
      "name": "Bard",
      "url": ""
    },
    "subclass": {
      "index": "college-of-valor",
      "name": "College of Valor",
      "url": ""
    },
    "desc": [
      "Starting at 6th level, you can attack twice, instead of once, whenever you take the Attack action on your turn."
    ],
    "url": ""
  },
  {
    "index": "battle-magic-college-of-valor",
    "name": "Battle Magic",
    "level": 14,
    "class": {
      "index": "bard",
      "name": "Bard",
      "url": ""
    },
    "subclass": {
      "index": "college-of-valor",
      "name": "College of Valor",
      "url": ""
    },
    "desc": [
      "At 14th level, you have mastered the art of weaving spellcasting and weapon use into a single harmonious act. When you use your action to cast a bard spell, you can make one weapon attack as a bonus action."
    ],
    "url": ""
  },
  {
    "index": "domain-spells-knowledge-domain",
