    "class": {
      "index": "cleric",
      "name": "Cleric",
      "url": ""
    },
    "subclass": {
      "index": "knowledge-domain",
      "name": "Knowledge Domain",
      "url": ""
    },
    "desc": [
      "1st level: command, identify. 3rd level: augury, suggestion. 5th level: nondetection, speak with dead. 7th level: arcane eye, confusion. 9th level: legend lore, scrying."
    ],
    "url": ""
  },
  {
    "index": "blessings-of-knowledge-knowledge-domain",
    "name": "Blessings of Knowledge",
    "level": 1,
    "class": {
      "index": "cleric",
      "name": "Cleric",
      "url": ""
    },
    "subclass": {
      "index": "knowledge-domain",
      "name": "Knowledge Domain",
      "url": ""
    },
    "desc": [
      "At 1st level, you learn two languages of your choice. You also become proficient in your choice of two of the following skills: Arcana, History, Nature, or Religion. Your proficiency bonus is doubled for any ability check you make that uses either of those skills."
    ],
    "url": ""
  },
  {
    "index": "channel-divinity-knowledge-of-the-ages-knowledge-domain",
    "name": "Channel Divinity: Knowledge of the Ages",
    "level": 2,
    "class": {
      "index": "cleric",
      "name": "Cleric",
      "url": ""
    },
    "subclass": {
      "index": "knowledge-domain",
      "name": "Knowledge Domain",
      "url": ""
    },
    "desc": [
      "Starting at 2nd level, you can use your Channel Divinity to tap into a divine well of knowledge. As an action, you choose one skill or tool. For 10 minutes, you have proficiency with the chosen skill or tool."
    ],
    "url": ""
  },
  {
    "index": "channel-divinity-read-thoughts-knowledge-domain",
    "name": "Channel Divinity: Read Thoughts",
    "level": 6,
    "class": {
      "index": "cleric",
      "name": "Cleric",
      "url": ""
    },
    "subclass": {
      "index": "knowledge-domain",
      "name": "Knowledge Domain",
      "url": ""
    },
    "desc": [
      "At 6th level, you can use your Channel Divinity to read a creature's thoughts and then use that access to command it. As an action, choose one creature you can see within 60 feet. That creature must make a Wisdom saving throw. On a success, you can't use this feature on it again until you finish a long rest. On a failure, you can read its surface thoughts (those foremost in its mind, reflecting its current emotions and what it is actively thinking about) while it is within 60 feet of you, for 1 minute. During that time, you can use your action to end the effect and cast suggestion on the creature without expending a spell slot; the target automatically fails its saving throw against the spell."
    ],
    "url": ""
  },
  {
    "index": "potent-spellcasting-knowledge-domain",
    "name": "Potent Spellcasting",
    "level": 8,
    "class": {
      "index": "cleric",
      "name": "Cleric",
      "url": ""
    },
    "subclass": {
      "index": "knowledge-domain",
      "name": "Knowledge Domain",
      "url": ""
    },
    "desc": [
      "Starting at 8th level, you add your Wisdom modifier to the damage you deal with any cleric cantrip."
    ],
    "url": ""
  },
  {
    "index": "visions-of-the-past-knowledge-domain",
    "name": "Visions of the Past",
    "level": 17,
    "class": {
      "index": "cleric",
      "name": "Cleric",
      "url": ""
    },
    "subclass": {
      "index": "knowledge-domain",
      "name": "Knowledge Domain",
      "url": ""
    },
    "desc": [
      "Starting at 17th level, you can call up visions of the past relating to an object you hold or your immediate surroundings. You spend at least 1 minute in meditation and prayer, then receive dreamlike, shadowy glimpses of recent events. You can meditate this way for a number of minutes equal to your Wisdom score and must maintain concentration, as if casting a spell. Once used, you can't use this feature again until you finish a short or long rest. Object Reading: holding an object as you meditate, you learn how its previous owner acquired and lost it, as well as the most recent significant event involving the object and that owner; if it was owned by another creature within a number of days equal to your Wisdom score, you can spend 1 additional minute per owner to learn the same about them. Area Reading: you see visions of recent events in your immediate vicinity (a room, street, tunnel, clearing, or similar up to a 50-foot cube), going back a number of days equal to your Wisdom score; for each minute you meditate, you learn about one significant event, beginning with the most recent."
    ],
    "url": ""
  },
  {
    "index": "domain-spells-light-domain",
    "name": "Domain Spells",
    "level": 1,
    "class": {
      "index": "cleric",
      "name": "Cleric",
      "url": ""
    },
    "subclass": {
      "index": "light-domain",
      "name": "Light Domain",
      "url": ""
    },
    "desc": [
      "1st level: burning hands, faerie fire. 3rd level: flaming sphere, scorching ray. 5th level: daylight, fireball. 7th level: guardian of faith, wall of fire. 9th level: flame strike, scrying."
    ],
    "url": ""
  },
  {
    "index": "bonus-cantrip-light-domain",
    "name": "Bonus Cantrip",
    "level": 1,
    "class": {
      "index": "cleric",
      "name": "Cleric",
      "url": ""
    },
    "subclass": {
      "index": "light-domain",
      "name": "Light Domain",
      "url": ""
    },
    "desc": [
      "When you choose this domain at 1st level, you gain the light cantrip if you don't already know it."
    ],
    "url": ""
  },
  {
    "index": "warding-flare-light-domain",
    "name": "Warding Flare",
    "level": 1,
    "class": {
      "index": "cleric",
      "name": "Cleric",
      "url": ""
    },
    "subclass": {
      "index": "light-domain",
      "name": "Light Domain",
      "url": ""
    },
    "desc": [
      "Also at 1st level, you can interpose divine light between yourself and an attacking enemy. When you are attacked by a creature within 30 feet of you that you can see, you can use your reaction to impose disadvantage on the attack roll, causing light to flare before the attacker before it hits or misses. An attacker that can't be blinded is immune to this feature. You can use this feature a number of times equal to your Wisdom modifier (a minimum of once). You regain all expended uses when you finish a long rest."
    ],
    "url": ""
  },
  {
    "index": "channel-divinity-radiance-of-the-dawn-light-domain",
