      "index": "way-of-shadow",
      "name": "Way of Shadow",
      "url": ""
    },
    "desc": [
      "At 17th level, you can exploit a creature's momentary distraction when it is hit by an attack. Whenever a creature within 5 feet of you is hit by an attack made by a creature other than you, you can use your reaction to make a melee attack against that creature."
    ],
    "url": ""
  },
  {
    "index": "disciple-of-the-elements-way-of-the-four-elements",
    "name": "Disciple of the Elements",
    "level": 3,
    "class": {
      "index": "monk",
      "name": "Monk",
      "url": ""
    },
    "subclass": {
      "index": "way-of-the-four-elements",
      "name": "Way of the Four Elements",
      "url": ""
    },
    "desc": [
      "When you choose this tradition at 3rd level, you learn magical disciplines that harness the power of the four elements. A discipline requires you to spend ki points each time you use it. You know the Elemental Attunement discipline and one other elemental discipline of your choice. You learn one additional elemental discipline at 6th, 11th, and 17th level, and each time you can also replace one you already know. The maximum ki points you can spend on a single use: 3 (levels 5-8), 4 (9-12), 5 (13-16), 6 (17-20). Available disciplines: Breath of Winter (17th, 6 ki, cone of cold); Clench of the North Wind (6th, 3 ki, hold person); Elemental Attunement (control elemental forces — create a sensory effect, light or snuff a small flame, chill or warm up to 1 pound of nonliving material for 1 hour, or shape earth/fire/water/mist in a 1-foot cube for 1 minute); Eternal Mountain Defense (11th, 5 ki, stoneskin on self); Fangs of the Fire Snake (1 ki on Attack action; unarmed reach +10 ft and deals fire damage; +1 ki on hit for extra 1d10 fire); Fist of Four Thunders (2 ki, thunderwave); Fist of Unbroken Air (2 ki; STR save or 3d10 bludgeoning, pushed 20 ft and knocked prone; +1d10 per extra ki, half on save); Flames of the Phoenix (11th, 4 ki, fireball); Gong of the Summit (6th, 3 ki, shatter); Mist Stance (11th, 4 ki, gaseous form on self); Ride the Wind (11th, 4 ki, fly on self); River of Hungry Flame (17th, 5 ki, wall of fire); Rush of the Gale Spirits (2 ki, gust of wind); Shape the Flowing River (1 ki, reshape ice or water in 30-ft area within 120 ft); Sweeping Cinder Strike (2 ki, burning hands); Water Whip (2 ki bonus action; DEX save or 3d10 bludgeoning and knocked prone or pulled 25 ft, +1d10 per extra ki); Wave of Rolling Earth (17th, 6 ki, wall of stone)."
    ],
    "url": ""
  },
  {
    "index": "oath-spells-oath-of-the-ancients",
