  {
    "index": "evocation",
    "class": {
      "index": "wizard",
      "name": "Wizard",
      "url": "/api/2014/classes/wizard"
    },
    "name": "Evocation",
    "subclass_flavor": "Arcane Tradition",
    "desc": [
      "You focus your study on magic that creates powerful elemental effects such as bitter cold, searing flame, rolling thunder, crackling lightning, and burning acid. Some evokers find employment in military forces, serving as artillery to blast enemy armies from afar. Others use their spectacular power to protect the weak, while some seek their own gain as bandits, adventurers, or aspiring tyrants."
    ],
    "subclass_levels": "/api/2014/subclasses/evocation/levels",
    "url": "/api/2014/subclasses/evocation"
  },
  {
    "index": "totem-warrior",
    "class": {
      "index": "barbarian",
      "name": "Barbarian",
      "url": ""
    },
    "name": "Totem Warrior",
    "subclass_flavor": "Primal Path",
    "desc": [
      "The Path of the Totem Warrior is a spiritual journey, as the barbarian accepts a spirit animal as guide, protector, and inspiration. In battle, your totem spirit fills you with supernatural might, adding magical fuel to your barbarian rage. Most barbarian tribes consider a totem animal to be kin to a particular clan."
    ],
    "url": ""
  },
  {
    "index": "college-of-valor",
    "class": {
      "index": "bard",
      "name": "Bard",
      "url": ""
    },
    "name": "College of Valor",
    "subclass_flavor": "Bard College",
    "desc": [
      "Bards of the College of Valor are daring skalds whose tales keep alive the memory of the great heroes of the past, inspiring a new generation. These bards gather in mead halls or around great bonfires to sing the deeds of the mighty, and travel the land to witness great events firsthand."
    ],
    "url": ""
  },
  {
    "index": "knowledge-domain",
    "class": {
      "index": "cleric",
      "name": "Cleric",
      "url": ""
    },
    "name": "Knowledge Domain",
    "subclass_flavor": "Divine Domain",
    "desc": [
      "The gods of knowledge value learning and understanding above all. Some teach that knowledge is to be gathered and shared in libraries and universities, or promote the practical knowledge of craft and invention. Followers study esoteric lore, collect old tomes, and delve into the secret places of the earth."
    ],
    "url": ""
  },
  {
    "index": "light-domain",
    "class": {
      "index": "cleric",
      "name": "Cleric",
      "url": ""
    },
    "name": "Light Domain",
    "subclass_flavor": "Divine Domain",
    "desc": [
      "Gods of light promote the ideals of rebirth and renewal, truth, vigilance, and beauty, often using the symbol of the sun. Clerics of a god of light are enlightened souls infused with radiance and the power of their gods' discerning vision, charged with chasing away lies and burning away darkness."
    ],
    "url": ""
  },
  {
    "index": "nature-domain",
    "class": {
      "index": "cleric",
      "name": "Cleric",
      "url": ""
    },
    "name": "Nature Domain",
    "subclass_flavor": "Divine Domain",
    "desc": [
      "Gods of nature are as varied as the natural world itself, from inscrutable gods of the deep forests to friendly deities associated with particular springs and groves. Their clerics are champions who take an active role in advancing the interests of a particular nature god — hunting evil monstrosities that despoil the woodlands, blessing the harvest of the faithful, or withering the crops of those who anger their gods."
    ],
    "url": ""
  },
  {
    "index": "tempest-domain",
    "class": {
      "index": "cleric",
      "name": "Cleric",
      "url": ""
    },
    "name": "Tempest Domain",
    "subclass_flavor": "Divine Domain",
    "desc": [
      "Gods whose portfolios include the Tempest domain govern storms, sea, and sky. They include gods of lightning and thunder, gods of earthquakes, and certain gods of violence, physical strength, and courage. Tempest clerics inspire fear in the common folk, either to keep them on the path of righteousness or to encourage offerings to ward off divine wrath."
    ],
    "url": ""
  },
  {
    "index": "trickery-domain",
    "class": {
      "index": "cleric",
      "name": "Cleric",
      "url": ""
    },
    "name": "Trickery Domain",
    "subclass_flavor": "Divine Domain",
    "desc": [
      "Gods of trickery are mischief-makers and instigators who stand as a constant challenge to the accepted order among both gods and mortals. They're patrons of thieves, scoundrels, gamblers, rebels, and liberators. Their clerics are a disruptive force in the world, preferring subterfuge, pranks, deception, and theft rather than direct confrontation."
    ],
    "url": ""
  },
  {
    "index": "war-domain",
    "class": {
      "index": "cleric",
      "name": "Cleric",
      "url": ""
    },
    "name": "War Domain",
    "subclass_flavor": "Divine Domain",
    "desc": [
      "War has many manifestations. It can make heroes of ordinary people, or be desperate and horrific. The gods of war watch over warriors and reward them for their great deeds. Clerics of such gods excel in battle, inspiring others to fight the good fight or offering acts of violence as prayers. War gods include champions of honor and chivalry, gods of destruction and pillage, and gods of conquest and domination."
    ],
    "url": ""
  },
  {
    "index": "circle-of-the-moon",
    "class": {
      "index": "druid",
      "name": "Druid",
      "url": ""
    },
    "name": "Circle of the Moon",
    "subclass_flavor": "Druid Circle",
    "desc": [
      "Druids of the Circle of the Moon are fierce guardians of the wilds. Their order gathers under the full moon to share news and trade warnings. They haunt the deepest parts of the wilderness and can shift between animal forms with ease — prowling as a great cat one night, soaring as an eagle the next day, and crashing through the undergrowth in bear form to drive off trespassers."
    ],
    "url": ""
  },
  {
    "index": "battle-master",
    "class": {
      "index": "fighter",
      "name": "Fighter",
      "url": ""
    },
    "name": "Battle Master",
    "subclass_flavor": "Martial Archetype",
    "desc": [
      "Those who emulate the Battle Master archetype employ martial techniques passed down through generations. To a Battle Master, combat is an academic field, sometimes including subjects beyond battle such as weaponsmithing and calligraphy. Battle Masters are well-rounded fighters of great skill and knowledge."
    ],
    "url": ""
  },
  {
    "index": "eldritch-knight",
    "class": {
      "index": "fighter",
      "name": "Fighter",
      "url": ""
    },
    "name": "Eldritch Knight",
    "subclass_flavor": "Martial Archetype",
    "desc": [
      "The Eldritch Knight combines the martial mastery common to all fighters with a careful study of magic. Eldritch Knights use magical techniques similar to those practiced by wizards, focusing their study on two of the eight schools of magic: abjuration and evocation."
    ],
    "url": ""
  },
  {
    "index": "way-of-shadow",
    "class": {
      "index": "monk",
      "name": "Monk",
      "url": ""
    },
    "name": "Way of Shadow",
    "subclass_flavor": "Monastic Tradition",
    "desc": [
      "Monks of the Way of Shadow follow a tradition that values stealth and subterfuge. These monks might be called ninjas or shadowdancers, and they serve as spies and assassins. Some monasteries are family clans sworn to secrecy about their arts and missions; others are more like thieves' guilds, hiring out their services to nobles, rich merchants, or anyone else who can pay."
    ],
    "url": ""
  },
  {
    "index": "way-of-the-four-elements",
    "class": {
      "index": "monk",
      "name": "Monk",
      "url": ""
    },
    "name": "Way of the Four Elements",
    "subclass_flavor": "Monastic Tradition",
    "desc": [
      "You follow a monastic tradition that teaches you to harness the elements. When you focus your ki, you can align yourself with the forces of creation and bend the four elements to your will, using them as an extension of your body."
    ],
    "url": ""
  },
  {
    "index": "oath-of-the-ancients",
    "class": {
      "index": "paladin",
      "name": "Paladin",
      "url": ""
    },
    "name": "Oath of the Ancients",
    "subclass_flavor": "Sacred Oath",
    "desc": [
      "The Oath of the Ancients is as old as the race of elves and the rituals of the druids. Sometimes called fey knights, green knights, or horned knights, paladins who swear this oath cast their lot with the side of the light in the cosmic struggle against darkness because they love the beautiful and life-giving things of the world, not necessarily because they believe in principles of honor, courage, and justice."
    ],
    "url": ""
  },
  {
    "index": "oath-of-vengeance",
    "class": {
      "index": "paladin",
      "name": "Paladin",
      "url": ""
    },
    "name": "Oath of Vengeance",
    "subclass_flavor": "Sacred Oath",
    "desc": [
      "The Oath of Vengeance is a solemn commitment to punish those who have committed a grievous sin. When evil forces slaughter helpless villagers, when an entire people turns against the will of the gods, when a thieves' guild grows too violent and powerful, when a dragon rampages through the countryside — at times like these, paladins arise and swear an Oath of Vengeance to set right that which has gone wrong."
    ],
    "url": ""
  },
  {
    "index": "beast-master",
    "class": {
      "index": "ranger",
      "name": "Ranger",
      "url": ""
    },
    "name": "Beast Master",
    "subclass_flavor": "Ranger Archetype",
    "desc": [
      "The Beast Master archetype embodies a friendship between the civilized races and the beasts of the world. United in focus, beast and ranger work as one to fight the monstrous foes that threaten civilization and the wilderness alike. Emulating this archetype means committing yourself to this ideal, working in partnership with an animal as its companion and friend."
    ],
    "url": ""
  },
  {
    "index": "assassin",
    "class": {
      "index": "rogue",
      "name": "Rogue",
      "url": ""
    },
    "name": "Assassin",
    "subclass_flavor": "Roguish Archetype",
    "desc": [
      "You focus your training on the grim art of death. Those who adhere to this archetype are diverse: hired killers, spies, bounty hunters, and even specially anointed priests trained to exterminate the enemies of their deity. Stealth, poison, and disguise help you eliminate your foes with deadly efficiency."
    ],
    "url": ""
  },
  {
    "index": "arcane-trickster",
    "class": {
      "index": "rogue",
      "name": "Rogue",
      "url": ""
    },
    "name": "Arcane Trickster",
    "subclass_flavor": "Roguish Archetype",
    "desc": [
      "Some rogues enhance their fine-honed skills of stealth and agility with magic, learning tricks of enchantment and illusion. These rogues include pickpockets and burglars, but also pranksters, mischief-makers, and a significant number of adventurers."
    ],
    "url": ""
  },
  {
    "index": "wild-magic",
    "class": {
      "index": "sorcerer",
      "name": "Sorcerer",
      "url": ""
    },
    "name": "Wild Magic",
    "subclass_flavor": "Sorcerous Origin",
    "desc": [
      "Your innate magic comes from the wild forces of chaos that underlie the order of creation. You might have endured exposure to some form of raw magic, perhaps through a planar portal or a mysterious blessing. However it came to be, this chaotic magic churns within you, waiting for any outlet."
    ],
    "url": ""
  },
  {
    "index": "the-archfey",
    "class": {
      "index": "warlock",
      "name": "Warlock",
      "url": ""
    },
    "name": "The Archfey",
    "subclass_flavor": "Otherworldly Patron",
    "desc": [
      "Your patron is a lord or lady of the fey, a creature of legend who holds secrets that were forgotten before the mortal races were born. This being's motivations are often inscrutable, and sometimes whimsical, and might involve a striving for greater magical power or the settling of age-old grudges."
    ],
    "url": ""
  },
  {
    "index": "the-great-old-one",
    "class": {
      "index": "warlock",
      "name": "Warlock",
      "url": ""
    },
    "name": "The Great Old One",
    "subclass_flavor": "Otherworldly Patron",
    "desc": [
      "Your patron is a mysterious entity whose nature is utterly foreign to the fabric of reality. It might come from the Far Realm, the space beyond reality, or it could be one of the elder gods known only in legends. Its motives are incomprehensible to mortals, and its knowledge so immense and ancient that even the greatest libraries pale in comparison."
    ],
    "url": ""
  },
  {
    "index": "school-of-abjuration",
    "class": {
      "index": "wizard",
      "name": "Wizard",
      "url": ""
    },
    "name": "School of Abjuration",
    "subclass_flavor": "Arcane Tradition",
    "desc": [
      "The School of Abjuration emphasizes magic that blocks, banishes, or protects. Detractors say its tradition is about denial — negation rather than positive assertion. You understand, however, that ending harmful effects, protecting the weak, and banishing evil influences is a proud and respected vocation."
    ],
    "url": ""
  },
  {
    "index": "school-of-conjuration",
    "class": {
      "index": "wizard",
      "name": "Wizard",
      "url": ""
    },
    "name": "School of Conjuration",
    "subclass_flavor": "Arcane Tradition",
    "desc": [
      "As a conjurer, you favor spells that produce objects and creatures out of thin air. You can conjure billowing clouds of killing fog or summon creatures from elsewhere to fight on your behalf. As your mastery grows, you learn spells of transportation and can teleport yourself across vast distances, even to other planes of existence, in an instant."
    ],
    "url": ""
  },
  {
    "index": "school-of-divination",
    "class": {
      "index": "wizard",
      "name": "Wizard",
      "url": ""
    },
    "name": "School of Divination",
    "subclass_flavor": "Arcane Tradition",
    "desc": [
      "The counsel of a diviner is sought by royalty and commoners alike, for all seek a clearer understanding of the past, present, and future. As a diviner, you strive to part the veils of space, time, and consciousness so that you can see clearly. You work to master spells of discernment, remote viewing, supernatural knowledge, and foresight."
    ],
    "url": ""
  },
  {
    "index": "school-of-enchantment",
    "class": {
      "index": "wizard",
      "name": "Wizard",
      "url": ""
    },
    "name": "School of Enchantment",
    "subclass_flavor": "Arcane Tradition",
    "desc": [
      "As a member of the School of Enchantment, you have honed your ability to magically entrance and beguile other people and monsters. Some enchanters are peacemakers who bewitch the violent to lay down their arms and charm the cruel into showing mercy. Others are tyrants who magically bind the unwilling into their service. Most enchanters fall somewhere in between."
    ],
    "url": ""
  },
  {
    "index": "school-of-illusion",
    "class": {
      "index": "wizard",
      "name": "Wizard",
      "url": ""
    },
    "name": "School of Illusion",
    "subclass_flavor": "Arcane Tradition",
    "desc": [
      "You focus your studies on magic that dazzles the senses, befuddles the mind, and tricks even the wisest folk. Your magic is subtle, but the illusions crafted by your keen mind make the impossible seem real. Some illusionists are benign tricksters who use their spells to entertain; others are sinister masters of deception."
    ],
    "url": ""
  },
  {
    "index": "school-of-necromancy",
    "class": {
      "index": "wizard",
      "name": "Wizard",
      "url": ""
    },
    "name": "School of Necromancy",
    "subclass_flavor": "Arcane Tradition",
    "desc": [
      "The School of Necromancy explores the cosmic forces of life, death, and undeath. As you focus your studies in this tradition, you learn to manipulate the energy that animates all living things, eventually sapping the life force from a creature as your magic destroys its body. Most people see necromancers as menacing, or even villainous, due to their close association with death."
    ],
    "url": ""
  },
  {
    "index": "school-of-transmutation",
    "class": {
      "index": "wizard",
      "name": "Wizard",
      "url": ""
    },
    "name": "School of Transmutation",
    "subclass_flavor": "Arcane Tradition",
    "desc": [
      "You are a student of spells that modify energy and matter. To you, the world is not a fixed thing, but eminently mutable, and you delight in being an agent of change. You wield the raw stuff of creation and learn to alter both physical forms and mental qualities. Some transmuters are tinkerers and pranksters; others pursue their studies with deadly seriousness, seeking the power of the gods to make and destroy worlds."
    ],
    "url": ""
  },
  {
    "index": "death-domain",
    "class": {
      "index": "cleric",
      "name": "Cleric",
      "url": "/api/2014/classes/cleric"
    },
    "name": "Death Domain",
    "subclass_flavor": "Divine Domain",
    "desc": [
      "The Death domain is concerned with the forces that cause death, as well as the negative energy that gives rise to undead creatures. Deities such as Chemosh, Myrkul, and Wee Jas are patrons of necromancers, death knights, liches, mummy lords, and vampires. Gods of the Death domain also embody murder (Anubis, Bhaal, and Pyremius), pain (Iuz or Loviatar), disease or poison (Incabulos, Talona, or Morgion), and the underworld (Hades and Hel)."
    ],
    "spells": [],
    "url": "/api/2014/subclasses/death-domain"
  },
  {
    "index": "oathbreaker",
    "class": {
      "index": "paladin",
      "name": "Paladin",
      "url": "/api/2014/classes/paladin"
    },
    "name": "Oathbreaker",
    "subclass_flavor": "Sacred Oath",
    "desc": [
      "An Oathbreaker is a paladin who breaks his or her sacred oaths to pursue some dark ambition or serve an evil power. Whatever light burned in the paladin's heart has been extinguished. Only darkness remains.",
      "A paladin must be evil and at least 3rd level to become an Oathbreaker. The paladin replaces the features specific to his or her Sacred Oath with Oathbreaker features.",
      "Atonement: If the DM allows, an Oathbreaker can later atone and become a true paladin once more. The paladin must first shed his or her evil alignment and demonstrate this through words and deeds. Having done so, the paladin loses all Oathbreaker features and must choose a deity and a sacred oath. However, the paladin doesn't gain the class features specific to that sacred oath until he or she completes some kind of dangerous quest or trial, as determined by the DM. A paladin who breaks his or her sacred oath a second time can become an oathbreaker once more, but can't atone."
    ],
    "spells": [],
    "url": "/api/2014/subclasses/oathbreaker"
  }
]